Let me look at `send_trans_email` again more carefully:

```javascript
exports.send_trans_email = function (transaction, next) {
    if (!transaction.header.get_all('Message-Id').length) {
        transaction.add_header('Message-Id', `<${transaction.uuid}@${net_utils.get_primary_host_name()}>`)
    }
    if (!transaction.header.get_all('Date').length) {
        transaction.add_header('Date', utils.date_to_str(new Date()))
    }
    if (obc.cfg.received_header !== 'disabled') {
        transaction.add_leading_header('Received', `(${obc.cfg.received_header}); ${utils.date_to_str(new Date())}`)
    }
    // ...
    plugins.run_hooks('pre_send_trans_email', connection)
}
```

Note: `add_header` and `add_leading_header` are called BEFORE `plugins.run_hooks('pre_send_trans_email', connection)`. The hook's callback (`pre_send_trans_email_respond`) then pipes the message. So these headers are added before piping. This should work.

BUT wait - look at the `send_email` function for the string case:

```javascript
transaction.add_data(Buffer.from(line)) // line 131
// ...
transaction.message_stream.add_line_end() // line 147

// Allow for the removal of Message-Id and/or Date headers
if (options.remove_msgid) {
    transaction.remove_header('Message-Id')
}
if (options.remove_date) {
    transaction.remove_header('Date')
}

this.send_trans_email(transaction, next)
```

Note: `add_line_end()` is called at line 147, BEFORE `remove_header` and `send_trans_email`. So `end_data` isn't called at all for the `send_email` flow! The data just goes through `add_data` and then `add_line_end()`.

But then in `send_trans_email`, `add_header` is called to add Message-Id and Date. These modify `header_list` (same as `message_stream.headers`). When piping, constructor headers are emitted.

Wait, but what about `header.parse()`? It's called automatically during `add_data` when EOH is found. So `header_list` gets populated. Then `add_header` appends. Then pipe emits constructor headers.

OK let me look at this from yet another angle. Let me look at the `queue/quarantine.js` to see if there's an issue there

